===Verb phrase===
'''to kick ass''' (''past tense and past participle'' '''kicked ass''')

#(''slang'') {{idiom}} To be very impressive.
#:''Your new car really kicks ass!''
#(''slang'') {{idiom}} To beat someone at something.
#:''You will kick his ass at tennis!''
#(''slang'') {{idiom}} To beat someone at a fight.
#:''You will kick his ass! He's going to look [[fucked up]]''

